  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ipaja Special Needs Social Enterprise &amp; Empowerment Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children with disabilities in Nigeria receive no support for life after school. This project pilots ideas to prepare children with disabilities to find work in their communities. Training facilities are provided to teach skills for jobs such as shoe making and tailoring, and apprenticeships are provided within the community. The project also ensures that the products are marketed and sold to ensure profit. The project is being carefully monitored with a view to replicating it in other schools.</narrative>
  </description>
